Package ohos.ivihardware.vehiclecontrol

Class VehicleVendorExtensionManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.ivihardware.vehiclecontrol.VehicleVendorExtensionManager

  • public class VehicleVendorExtensionManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A public class that obtains vehicle signal information defined by original equipment manufacturers (OEMs).

    This class provides signal access methods. You can use the methods to access custom vehicle signals defined by OEMs.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Ivi.VehicleControl

      • getVehicleSignal

        public static <T> T getVehicleSignal​(java.lang.Class<T> propClass,
                                     java.lang.String propertyId,
                                     int zone)
                              throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                     ohos.rpc.RemoteException
        Obtains the signal value of a vehicle.

        You can obtain the signal value of only the specified signal in a vehicle zone. You must use a variable whose data type is the same as that of the specified signal to save the result.

        Sample code for obtaining the signal value of a vehicle: 

         String signalValue = VehicleVendorExtensionManager.getVehicleSignal(String.class,
             "VENDOR_WINDSHIELD_WIPING_STATUS", VehicleZone.ZONE_FRONT);
        Parameters:
        propClass - Indicates the data type wrapper for the specified signal, for example, Long.class.
        propertyId - Identifies a vehicle signal, which can be of the attribute, signal, or actuator type.
        zone - Indicates the vehicle zone (default value: entire vehicle), which is defined in VehicleZone. All options of the zone signal have been listed in the description of the propertyId for each vehicle.
        Returns:
        Returns the signal value. Returns the signal value of the boolean, byte, short, int, long, float, double, or string type.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if a parameter value is invalid.
        ohos.rpc.RemoteException - Throws this exception if an IPC error occurs.
        Since:
        1

      • getVehicleSignalMultiAreas

        public static <T> java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,T> getVehicleSignalMultiAreas​(java.lang.Class<T> propClass,
                                                                                java.lang.String propertyId,
                                                                                int zone)
                                                                         throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                                                                ohos.rpc.RemoteException,
                                                                                java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
        Obtains the values of a specified signal from multiple vehicle zones.

        The data type can be boolean, byte, short, integer, long, float, double, or string. You must use a map whose value type is the same as that of the specified signal to save the result.

        Sample code for obtaining signal values from multiple vehicle zones: 

         int zone = VehicleZone.ZONE_ROW1;
 Map<Integer, Boolean> valueMap = VehicleVendorExtensionManager.getVehicleSignalMultiAreas
 (Boolean.class, "VENDOR_WINDSHIELD_WIPING_STATUS", zone);
        Parameters:
        propClass - Indicates the data type wrapper for the specified signal, for example, Long.class.
        propertyId - Identifies the vehicle signal. The node type can be attribute, signal, or actuator.
        zone - Indicates the vehicle zone, which is defined in VehicleZone. For example, the value ZONE_NONE indicates all the vehicle zones for a specified signal, and the value ZONE_ROW1 indicates that the left and right areas of the first row.
        Returns:
        Returns a map of key-value pairs to store the signal values from multiple vehicle zones. In the map, keys are the vehicle zones defined in VehicleZone, and values are the signal values from the specified zones. The data type can be boolean, byte, short, integer, long, float, double, or string.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - Throws this exception if the signal is unavailable.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if a parameter value is invalid.
        ohos.rpc.RemoteException - Throws this exception if an IPC error occurs.
        Since:
        3

      • setVehicleActuator

        public static <T> void setVehicleActuator​(java.lang.String propertyId,
                                          int zone,
                                          VehicleActuatorCallback callback,
                                          T value)
                                   throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                          ohos.rpc.RemoteException
        Sets the actuator value of a vehicle.

        The actuator can be a unique signal in the entire vehicle or a signal of the same type in a zone of the vehicle. If the setting is successful, no value is returned.

        Sample code for setting the actuator value of a vehicle: 

         String propId = "VENDOR_WINDSHIELD_WIPING_STATUS";
 int zoneId = VehicleZone.ZONE_NONE;
 Boolean value = false;
 VehicleActuatorCallback callback = new VehicleActuatorCallback() {
     @Override
     public void onErrorActuator(String propId, int zoneId, int outResult) {
     }
 };
 VehicleVendorExtensionManager.setVehicleActuator(propId, zoneId, callback, value);
        Parameters:
        propertyId - Identifies a vehicle signal, which can be of the actuator type.
        zone - Indicates the vehicle zone (default value: entire vehicle), which is defined in VehicleZone. All options of the zone signal have been listed in the description of the propertyId for each vehicle. Multiple values of zone can be combined, for example, you can set zone to ZONE_ROW1 | ZONE_POS1 and ZONE_ROW1 | ZONE_POS2 to get their intersection ZONE_ROW1.
        callback - Indicates the setting error callback.
        value - Indicates the assigned signal value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if a parameter value is invalid.
        ohos.rpc.RemoteException - Throws this exception if an IPC error occurs.
        Since:
        1

      • subscribeVehicleSignal

        public static VsSubscription subscribeVehicleSignal​(java.lang.String propertyId,
                                                    int zone,
                                                    VehicleSignalCallback vehicleVendorCallback,
                                                    SubscriberFilter filters)
                                             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                                    ohos.rpc.RemoteException
        Subscribes to the signal value of a vehicle.

        This is an asynchronous method. The signal value must be of only the specified signal in a vehicle zone.

        Sample code for subscribing to the signal value of a vehicle: 

         private class VehicleVendorExtensionManagerTestSubCallback implements VehicleSignalCallback {
     @Override
     public void onChangeSignal(PropertyInfo propInfo) {
     }
     @Override
     public void onErrorSignal(String propId, int zoneId, int errorCode) {
     }
 }
 SubscriberFilter testFilter = new SubscriberFilter();
 VehicleVendorExtensionManagerTestSubCallback testCallback = new VehicleVendorExtensionManagerTestSubCallback();
 String propId = "VENDOR_WINDSHIELD_WIPING_STATUS";
 int zoneId = VehicleZone.ZONE_FRONT;
 VsSubscription result = VehicleVendorExtensionManager.subscribeVehicleSignal(propId, zoneId, testCallback,
 testFilter);
        Parameters:
        propertyId - Identifies a vehicle signal, which can be of the actuator and sensor type.
        zone - Indicates the vehicle zone (default value: entire vehicle), which is defined in VehicleZone. All options of the zone signal have been listed in the description of the propertyId for each vehicle.
        vehicleVendorCallback - Indicates the callback function of the subscription.
        filters - Indicates the subscription policy (SubscriberFilter), which can be interval, range, or minchange. This parameter can be default (interval 200ms, below Long.MIN_VAL, above Long.MAX_VAL, minchange 1).
        Returns:
        Returns VsSubscription if subscription is successful.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if a parameter value is invalid.
        ohos.rpc.RemoteException - Throws this exception if an IPC error occurs.
        Since:
        4

      • unsubscribeVehicleSignal

        public static void unsubscribeVehicleSignal​(VsSubscription subscription)
                                     throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                            ohos.rpc.RemoteException
        Unsubscribes from the signal of a vehicle with the VsSubscription handle.

        No exception is thrown if the unsubscription is successful.

        Sample code for unsubscribing to the signal value of a vehicle: 

         private class VehicleVendorManagerTestSubCallback implements VehicleSignalCallback {
     @Override
     public void onChangeSignal(PropertyInfo propInfo) {
     }
     @Override
     public void onErrorSignal(String propId, int zoneId, int errorCode) {
     }
 }
 SubscriberFilter testFilter = new SubscriberFilter();
 VehicleVendorManagerTestSubCallback testCallback = new VehicleVendorManagerTestSubCallback();
 String propId = "VENDOR_WINDSHIELD_WIPING_STATUS";
 int zoneId = VehicleZone.ZONE_FRONT;
 VsSubscription result = new VsSubscription();
 result = VehicleVendorExtensionManager.subscribeVehicleSignal(propId, zoneId, testCallback, testFilter);
 VehicleVendorExtensionManager.unsubscribeVehicleSignal(result);
        Parameters:
        subscription - Identifies a subscription.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if a parameter value is invalid.
        ohos.rpc.RemoteException - Throws this exception if an IPC error occurs.
        Since:
        1
